channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Georgia attorney general appeals a judge's rollback of abortion ban
item.description: Georgia's Republican attorney general is appealing a judge's ruling that the state's abortion ban is unconstitutional

item.title: Destruction in southern Lebanese city of Nabatieh after intensive Israeli airstrikes
MS-13 associate dubbed "La Diablita" sentenced to 50 years in prison
item.description: The woman convicted of luring five young men into a Long Island park where they were attacked by MS-13 gang members that killed four of them​ was sentenced to 50 years in prison Tuesday.

item.title: Michael Jordan's 23XI and a 2nd team sue NASCAR over revenue sharing model
item.description: NASCAR is facing a federal antitrust lawsuit from two of its teams, including one co-owned by Michael Jordan

item.title: Another setback for Elon Musk's SpaceX after mishap with NASA rescue mission
Jess Glynne returns to the U.S. with new tour
item.description: Jess Glynne, known for her hit "Don't Be So Hard on Yourself," is back in the U.S. following the release of her third album, "Jess." She joins "CBS Mornings Plus" to talk about her new tour.

item.title: 2 explosions rock the area around the Israeli Embassy in Copenhagen
item.description: Three Swedish nationals have been arrested in connection with two predawn explosions in the vicinity of the Israeli Embassy in Copenhagen

item.title: Mexico’s first female president promises ‘no return to drug war’
How the Vance-Walz debate played to undecided voters
item.description: Vice presidential candidates JD Vance and Tim Walz squared off in a policy-focused debate Tuesday night that's being praised for its civility. CBS News political director Fin Gómez has more on the takeaways from each candidate's performance and CBS News national correspondent Jericka Duncan reports on how some voters are reacting.

item.title: WATCH: Meet the Walt Disney World custodian who brings magic to guests with their water art
item.description: In addition to keeping the parks clean and tidy, Walt Disney World custodian Joel Hernandez Rodriguez spreads joy by drawing Disney characters on the pavement with his unique water artwork.

item.title: A US bomb from World War II explodes at a Japanese airport, causing a large crater in a taxiway
Colin Kaepernick and Nessa Diab on continuing activism through children's literature
item.description: Former NFL quarterback Colin Kaepernick and media personality Nessa Diab are with "CBS Mornings" for their first TV interview together. The couple co-founded the "Know Your Rights Camp" in 2015 with the mission of advancing the well-being of Black and Brown communities, through education and self-empowerment. Now, they are releasing their new children's book called "We Are Free, You and Me."

item.title: WATCH: Competitors aim for speed at World Jigsaw Championships
item.description: For most people, jigsaw puzzles are a relaxing pastime, but competitors feel the need for speed at the World Jigsaw Championships.

item.title: This nearby dwarf planet's ice may be left over from a dirty ocean
How swing state voters viewed the vice presidential debate
item.description: CBS News correspondent Jericka Duncan watched Tuesday's VP debate in the politically diverse city of Grand Rapids, Michigan. People in the area voted for former President Donald Trump in 2016 and President Biden in 2020. A group of voters who are split on the candidates react to who they think won the debate.
